    </section>

    <SectionDivider variant="default" spacing="normal" />

    <!-- ================================================================ -->
    <!-- SECTION 2 ‚Äî Systems View -->
    <!-- ================================================================ -->
    <section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="systems-title">
      <SectionHeader
        title="A Systems View"
        subtitle="Where technology, ecology, and culture meet."
        align="center"
      />

      <p>
        I‚Äôve always been drawn to how systems interconnect ‚Äî biological, technological, and social.  
        Through ArcUp, I explore how plasma, data, and design can support living systems rather than extract from them.
      </p>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <Card as="article" variant="surface">
          <h3>Interdisciplinary Practice</h3>
          <p>
            ArcUp sits between biology, physics, ethics, and design ‚Äî inviting each field to inform the others.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card as="article" variant="outline">
          <h3>Ecological Thinking</h3>
          <p>
            Every technical decision carries ecological weight; regeneration, not exploitation, is the measure of success.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <p>
        Science, to me, is strongest when it listens ‚Äî to ecosystems, to context, and to the people it serves.
      </p>
    </section>

    <SectionDivider variant="strong" spacing="normal" />

    <!-- ================================================================ -->
    <!-- SECTION 3 ‚Äî Personal Ethos -->
    <!-- ================================================================ -->
    <section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="ethos-title">
      <SectionHeader
        title="Personal Ethos"
        subtitle="Principles that guide my research and design practice."
        align="center"
      />

      <div class="card-grid">
        <Card as="article" variant="outline">
          <h3>Openness over Ownership</h3>
          <p>
            Knowledge belongs in the commons ‚Äî science should circulate, not accumulate.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card as="article" variant="outline">
          <h3>Curiosity over Control</h3>
          <p>
            I approach research as an act of humility ‚Äî a conversation with the unknown.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card as="article" variant="outline">
          <h3>Regeneration over Recognition</h3>
          <p>
            The goal isn‚Äôt acclaim; it‚Äôs repair ‚Äî restoring balance between innovation and the living systems that sustain it.
          </p>
